+- R2-M2 [verify]: partially addressed in `6c53986` — the contract narrative removed the old hard `<2%` plateau claim, but the anchor block still stores `6.26` under a Le/Moin/Kim 1997 source that the same file describes as `6.28`, and the observable description still repeats the `<2%` drift language (`knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:16-18`, `knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:35-42`).
